{"role":"assistant","type":"tool_use","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Design zip download implementation","subagent_type":"Plan","prompt":"Based on the comprehensive exploration results, design an implementation plan for creating zip file downloads of all documents and certificates for personnel records.\n\n## Context from Exploration:\n\n**Personnel System:**\n- Personnel records stored in PostgreSQL with comprehensive fields (names, company, training status, etc.)\n- Role-based access control (ADMIN, OVERSIGHT, OWNER, INSTRUCTOR)\n- Access patterns: Owners see their company personnel, instructors see assigned personnel, admins see all\n- API endpoint: /api/personnel/search for finding personnel\n\n**Document/Certificate Management:**\n- Documents stored in Google Cloud Storage (bucket: ofca-2026)\n- Database table: `documents` with personnelId, fileName, fileUrl (GCS path)\n- GCS utility functions: downloadFile(), generatePersonnelDocumentPath()\n- Certificate generation: Dynamic from training records, requires payment\n- Photo storage: personnel photos at photos/personnel/{id}.jpg\n\n**Existing Download Patterns:**\n- CSV exports use: new Response(content, {headers: {\"Content-Type\": \"...\", \"Content-Disposition\": \"attachment; filename=...\"}})\n- File streaming: downloadFile() returns {buffer, contentType}, then new Response(new Uint8Array(buffer))\n- Bulk operations: Promise.all() for concurrent processing\n- Access control: requireUser(), role checks before returning data\n\n## Requirements:\n1. Create zip downloads containing all documents AND certificates for a personnel record\n2. Maintain existing role-based access control\n3. Include personnel photos if available\n4. Include generated certificates from training records\n5. Handle cases where personnel have no documents gracefully\n6. Use existing patterns and utilities where possible\n\nDesign a comprehensive implementation plan including:\n- API endpoint design\n- Frontend UI integration points\n- File bundling approach\n- Access control implementation\n- Error handling strategy\n- Performance considerations"},"timestamp":1772733101484}
