{"role":"assistant","type":"tool_use","name":"AskUserQuestion","input":{"questions":[{"question":"Should unpaid training certificates be included in the zip download?","header":"Certificates","multiSelect":false,"options":[{"label":"Only paid certificates (Recommended)","description":"Follow existing pattern where certificates require payment before viewing/printing. This maintains consistency with current certificate access rules."},{"label":"Include all certificates","description":"Include both paid and unpaid certificates in the zip download, with clear marking of payment status."},{"label":"Skip certificates entirely","description":"Only include uploaded documents and personnel photos, excluding generated certificates from training records."}]},{"question":"Where should the download button be accessible?","header":"UI Location","multiSelect":false,"options":[{"label":"Individual personnel page only (Recommended)","description":"Add download button to the personnel detail page (/personnel/$id). Simple to implement and aligns with individual record management."},{"label":"Both individual and bulk operations","description":"Add to personnel detail page plus bulk download options from personnel list page and company dashboards."}]}]},"timestamp":1772733279718}
{"role":"assistant","type":"tool_use","name":"ExitPlanMode","input":{"allowedPrompts":[],"plan":"# Personnel Document & Certificate Zip Downloads\n\n## Context\n\nThis feature addresses the need for personnel to easily export all their documents and certificates for record-keeping when they leave or transfer between organizations. Currently, users must individually download each document, which is cumbersome for personnel with extensive training records.\n\nThe system already has robust document management with Google Cloud Storage, certificate generation from training records, role-based access control, and file download patterns that can be leveraged for this implementation.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Add ZIP Dependency\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/package.json`\n- Add `jszip: \"^3.10.1\"` dependency for ZIP file creation\n\n### Phase 2: Create ZIP Utility Module\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/app/lib/zip.server.ts`\n- `createPersonnelZip(personnelId: string, user: User, isImpersonating: boolean): Promise<Buffer>`\n- Leverage existing `downloadFile()` from GCS utility\n- Use `Promise.all()` for concurrent file downloads (following `/api/announcements.tsx` pattern)\n- Handle partial failures gracefully (continue with available files)\n\n**ZIP Structure:**\n```\n{firstName}_{lastName}_{personnelId}/\n├── Documents/           # All uploaded documents\n│   ├── document1.pdf\n│   └── document2.jpg\n├── Certificates/        # Generated training certificates\n│   ├── RT-130_certificate.pdf\n│   └── Pack_Test_certificate.pdf\n└── Photos/\n    └── personnel_photo.jpg\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Create API Endpoint\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/api.personnel.zip-download.tsx`\n- GET endpoint with personnelId query parameter\n- Follow exact access control pattern from `/api/documents.personnel.tsx`:\n  - Use `requireUser()` for authentication\n  - Use `canAccessPersonnelAsync()` for authorization\n- Query documents: `SELECT * FROM documents WHERE personnelId = ?`\n- Query training certificates: Join training/classes/instructors tables for certificate data\n- Follow CSV export response pattern from `/api/training.export.tsx`:\n  ```typescript\n  return new Response(zipBuffer, {\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/zip\",\n      \"Content-Disposition\": `attachment; filename=\"${firstName}_${lastName}_documents.zip\"`,\n    },\n  });\n  ```\n\n### Phase 4: Frontend Integration\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/personnel.$id.tsx`\n- Add \"Download All Documents\" button in documents section\n- Place near existing document upload functionality\n- Use existing button styling patterns from the page\n- Handle loading state during ZIP generation\n- Use `useFetcher()` for non-blocking download request\n\n**Button Implementation:**\n```typescript\n<button\n  onClick={() => window.open(`/api/personnel/zip-download?id=${personnel.id}`)}\n  className=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700\"\n>\n  <Download className=\"h-4 w-4\" />\n  Download All Documents\n</button>\n```\n\n### Phase 5: Certificate Generation Integration\n\n**Leverage existing certificate routes:**\n- `/certificates.$trainingId.tsx` - Individual certificate rendering logic\n- `/classes.$id.certificates.tsx` - Bulk certificate queries\n- Reuse payment checking logic (`training.paidOn !== null`)\n- Generate PDF certificates server-side (consider headless browser or PDF library)\n\n### Critical Files to Modify\n\n1. **`/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/api.personnel.zip-download.tsx`** - New API endpoint\n2. **`/vercel/sandbox/app/lib/zip.server.ts`** - Core ZIP creation utility\n3. **`/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/personnel.$id.tsx`** - Add download button\n4. **`/vercel/sandbox/package.json`** - Add jszip dependency\n\n### Existing Utilities to Reuse\n\n- **GCS Operations:** `downloadFile()`, `generatePersonnelPhotoPath()` from `/app/lib/gcs.server.ts`\n- **Access Control:** `canAccessPersonnelAsync()` from `/app/lib/roles.server.ts`\n- **Database Queries:** Document/training patterns from `/api/documents.personnel.tsx`\n- **Response Handling:** CSV export pattern from `/api/training.export.tsx`\n- **Concurrent Processing:** `Promise.all()` pattern from `/api/announcements.tsx`\n\n### Error Handling & Performance\n\n- **Partial Success:** Continue ZIP creation even if individual files fail to download\n- **Memory Management:** Stream ZIP creation for large document sets\n- **Timeout Protection:** Reasonable limits on ZIP generation time\n- **Access Control:** Strict enforcement using existing role-based patterns\n- **Legacy Bucket Support:** Leverage GCS utility's automatic fallback handling\n\n### Verification Steps\n\n1. **Role-based Access:** Test with different user roles (Owner, Instructor, Admin)\n2. **File Types:** Verify various document formats and personnel photos are included\n3. **Certificate Generation:** Ensure paid certificates are included, unpaid ones handled appropriately\n4. **Large Document Sets:** Test performance with personnel having many documents\n5. **Error Scenarios:** Verify graceful handling of missing files or access failures\n6. **ZIP Structure:** Confirm proper folder organization and filename handling\n\nThis implementation leverages all existing patterns and utilities, ensuring consistency with the current architecture while providing a valuable new feature for personnel record management."},"timestamp":1772733286853}
{"role":"assistant","type":"tool_use","name":"ExitPlanMode","input":{"allowedPrompts":[{"tool":"Bash","prompt":"install npm packages"},{"tool":"Bash","prompt":"commit and push changes"},{"tool":"Bash","prompt":"create pull request"}],"plan":"# Personnel Document & Certificate Zip Downloads\n\n## Context\n\nThis feature addresses the need for personnel to easily export all their documents and certificates for record-keeping when they leave or transfer between organizations. Currently, users must individually download each document, which is cumbersome for personnel with extensive training records.\n\nThe system already has robust document management with Google Cloud Storage, certificate generation from training records, role-based access control, and file download patterns that can be leveraged for this implementation.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Add ZIP Dependency\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/package.json`\n- Add `jszip: \"^3.10.1\"` dependency for ZIP file creation\n\n### Phase 2: Create ZIP Utility Module\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/app/lib/zip.server.ts`\n- `createPersonnelZip(personnelId: string, user: User, isImpersonating: boolean): Promise<Buffer>`\n- Leverage existing `downloadFile()` from GCS utility\n- Use `Promise.all()` for concurrent file downloads (following `/api/announcements.tsx` pattern)\n- Handle partial failures gracefully (continue with available files)\n\n**ZIP Structure:**\n```\n{firstName}_{lastName}_{personnelId}/\n├── Documents/           # All uploaded documents\n│   ├── document1.pdf\n│   └── document2.jpg\n├── Certificates/        # Generated training certificates\n│   ├── RT-130_certificate.pdf\n│   └── Pack_Test_certificate.pdf\n└── Photos/\n    └── personnel_photo.jpg\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Create API Endpoint\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/api.personnel.zip-download.tsx`\n- GET endpoint with personnelId query parameter\n- Follow exact access control pattern from `/api/documents.personnel.tsx`:\n  - Use `requireUser()` for authentication\n  - Use `canAccessPersonnelAsync()` for authorization\n- Query documents: `SELECT * FROM documents WHERE personnelId = ?`\n- Query training certificates: Join training/classes/instructors tables for certificate data\n- Follow CSV export response pattern from `/api/training.export.tsx`:\n  ```typescript\n  return new Response(zipBuffer, {\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/zip\",\n      \"Content-Disposition\": `attachment; filename=\"${firstName}_${lastName}_documents.zip\"`,\n    },\n  });\n  ```\n\n### Phase 4: Frontend Integration\n\n**File:** `/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/personnel.$id.tsx`\n- Add \"Download All Documents\" button in documents section\n- Place near existing document upload functionality\n- Use existing button styling patterns from the page\n- Handle loading state during ZIP generation\n- Use `useFetcher()` for non-blocking download request\n\n**Button Implementation:**\n```typescript\n<button\n  onClick={() => window.open(`/api/personnel/zip-download?id=${personnel.id}`)}\n  className=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700\"\n>\n  <Download className=\"h-4 w-4\" />\n  Download All Documents\n</button>\n```\n\n### Phase 5: Certificate Generation Integration\n\n**Leverage existing certificate routes:**\n- `/certificates.$trainingId.tsx` - Individual certificate rendering logic\n- `/classes.$id.certificates.tsx` - Bulk certificate queries\n- Reuse payment checking logic (`training.paidOn !== null`)\n- Generate PDF certificates server-side (consider headless browser or PDF library)\n\n### Critical Files to Modify\n\n1. **`/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/api.personnel.zip-download.tsx`** - New API endpoint\n2. **`/vercel/sandbox/app/lib/zip.server.ts`** - Core ZIP creation utility\n3. **`/vercel/sandbox/app/routes/personnel.$id.tsx`** - Add download button\n4. **`/vercel/sandbox/package.json`** - Add jszip dependency\n\n### Existing Utilities to Reuse\n\n- **GCS Operations:** `downloadFile()`, `generatePersonnelPhotoPath()` from `/app/lib/gcs.server.ts`\n- **Access Control:** `canAccessPersonnelAsync()` from `/app/lib/roles.server.ts`\n- **Database Queries:** Document/training patterns from `/api/documents.personnel.tsx`\n- **Response Handling:** CSV export pattern from `/api/training.export.tsx`\n- **Concurrent Processing:** `Promise.all()` pattern from `/api/announcements.tsx`\n\n### Error Handling & Performance\n\n- **Partial Success:** Continue ZIP creation even if individual files fail to download\n- **Memory Management:** Stream ZIP creation for large document sets\n- **Timeout Protection:** Reasonable limits on ZIP generation time\n- **Access Control:** Strict enforcement using existing role-based patterns\n- **Legacy Bucket Support:** Leverage GCS utility's automatic fallback handling\n\n### Verification Steps\n\n1. **Role-based Access:** Test with different user roles (Owner, Instructor, Admin)\n2. **File Types:** Verify various document formats and personnel photos are included\n3. **Certificate Generation:** Ensure paid certificates are included, unpaid ones handled appropriately\n4. **Large Document Sets:** Test performance with personnel having many documents\n5. **Error Scenarios:** Verify graceful handling of missing files or access failures\n6. **ZIP Structure:** Confirm proper folder organization and filename handling\n\nThis implementation leverages all existing patterns and utilities, ensuring consistency with the current architecture while providing a valuable new feature for personnel record management."},"timestamp":1772733295659}
