wnload button\n4. **`/vercel/sandbox/package.json`** - Add jszip dependency\n\n### Existing Utilities to Reuse\n\n- **GCS Operations:** `downloadFile()`, `generatePersonnelPhotoPath()` from `/app/lib/gcs.server.ts`\n- **Access Control:** `canAccessPersonnelAsync()` from `/app/lib/roles.server.ts`\n- **Database Queries:** Document/training patterns from `/api/documents.personnel.tsx`\n- **Response Handling:** CSV export pattern from `/api/training.export.tsx`\n- **Concurrent Processing:** `Promise.all()` pattern from `/api/announcements.tsx`\n\n### Error Handling & Performance\n\n- **Partial Success:** Continue ZIP creation even if individual files fail to download\n- **Memory Management:** Stream ZIP creation for large document sets\n- **Timeout Protection:** Reasonable limits on ZIP generation time\n- **Access Control:** Strict enforcement using existing role-based patterns\n- **Legacy Bucket Support:** Leverage GCS utility's automatic fallback handling\n\n### Verification Steps\n\n1. **Role-based Access:** Test with different user roles (Owner, Instructor, Admin)\n2. **File Types:** Verify various document formats and personnel photos are included\n3. **Certificate Generation:** Ensure paid certificates are included, unpaid ones handled appropriately\n4. **Large Document Sets:** Test performance with personnel having many documents\n5. **Error Scenarios:** Verify graceful handling of missing files or access failures\n6. **ZIP Structure:** Confirm proper folder organization and filename handling\n\nThis implementation leverages all existing patterns and utilities, ensuring consistency with the current architecture while providing a valuable new feature for personnel record management."},"timestamp":1772733332595}
